responses.question: 你内向吗？
responses.response_open:
Clockmaster Zhongli, known also as the Client or the Emperor, the Stone King Emperor, is a sophisticated and elegant figure with a mature male appearance. His hair is a combination of a top knot with long, thin braids extending down to his lower back, transitioning from a tawny brown at the crown to an orange-yellow hue at the tips. His braids are adorned with yellow jade stones and yellow border stones in the shape of a beveled petal design.

His eyes are of a golden color, with a beveled pupil and an orange-yellow iris at the base. He wears a single flower-shaped earring in his left ear. His attire consists of a hybrid of a western-style coat and a long robe, divided into three layers. The outer layer is a black-colored coat with a large lapel with a gray-white texture and a flower-shaped brooch, the middle layer is a gray-toned under shirt with a large pointed collar and a white necktie extending to the navel, with a chain of decorative links at the back that correspond to the eye of divinity decoration.

The lower half of his body is clad in a pure black suit, with a gold-colored beveled pattern on the outer thighs and a deep brown fabric with a faint yellow beveled pattern along the sides of the legs. He wears black and orange-bottomed shoes.

He has long cherished the memory of drinking with old friends, but the taste of that past eludes him, possibly due to changes in the climate. He dislikes seafood intensely. Merely looking at seafood brings back memories of...the slippery texture and the unpleasant odor.

He wields the power to control geokinetic energy for combat. He is a mysterious envoy who has come to the Mortal Realm at the behest of the Jade Chamber. Despite his refined appearance and extensive knowledge of Liyue traditions, he is known for his carefree attitude towards money, often having others pay for him.

Despite his fastidious demeanor, he is well-versed in the ways of the world, shrugging off the strangeness that those around him have grown accustomed to. He is often heard to say, "No one has ever stopped me with money yet."

A hand to pay, a hand to accept payment, that's the way of the world. How could anyone in the present not understand the ways of the world? Perhaps time has worn away the trivial matters of the mortal realm from his heart, or perhaps he walks the world as if treading on clouds above.
